cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use GlycoTwin, please cite it as below."
title: "GlycoTwin: a mechanistic, interactive digital twin for antibody N-glycosylation in CHO cell culture"
abstract: >-
  GlycoTwin links controllable bioreactor parameters to the N-glycan critical
  quality attributes of an IgG1 Fc glycan through a mechanistic model: a 9-state
  fed-batch CHO bioreactor ODE feeds an ER to Golgi enzyme train driven by the two
  real control levers, Golgi glycosyltransferases and nucleotide-sugar donors.
  It provides interactive simulation, ICH-Q8 design-space exploration, Monte-Carlo
  robustness, PID control with disturbance rejection, and a governed agent optimizer,
  delivered as a single offline HTML file plus an optional FastAPI backend.
type: software
